   JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oid
   WHERE o.deltajd >= 365
   GROUP BY o.oid

         AND f.value > 0.5)-- r band

    FROM probability

    SELECT o.oid
    FROM object o
    JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oid
    WHERE o.deltajd >= 365
    GROUP BY o.oid
    HAVING MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
        OR MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
        OR MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 3 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
),

-- Subquery to get OIDs of objects with required magnitude variations
magnitude_variations AS (
    SELECT f.oid
    FROM feature f
    WHERE (f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.value - (SELECT MIN(value) FROM feature WHERE oid = f.oid AND name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND fid = 1) > 1)
       OR (f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.value - (SELECT MIN(value) FROM feature WHERE oid = f.oid AND name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND fid = 2) > 0.5)
)

       o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,
       MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END) AS max_g_mag,
       MIN(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END) AS min_g_mag,
       MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 2 THEN f.value END) AS max_r_mag,

JOIN feature f ON o.oid = f.oid

    WHERE class_name = 'AGN'
      AND probability > 0.6
      AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
      AND ranking = 1
),

-- Subquery to get OIDs of objects with light curves covering at least one year and at least 20 detections in one band
valid_objects AS (
    SELECT o.oid
    FROM object o
    JOIN detection d ON o.oid = d.oid
    WHERE o.deltajd >= 365
    GROUP BY o.oid
    HAVING MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
        OR MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
        OR MAX(CASE WHEN d.fid = 3 THEN d.ndet ELSE 0 END) >= 20
),

-- Subquery to get OIDs of objects with required magnitude variations
magnitude_variations AS (
    SELECT f.oid
    FROM feature f
    WHERE (f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.value - (SELECT MIN(value) FROM feature WHERE oid = f.oid AND name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND fid = 1) > 1)
       OR (f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.value - (SELECT MIN(value) FROM feature WHERE oid = f.oid AND name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND fid = 2) > 0.5)
)

-- Main query to select the required information
SELECT o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid AS feature_fid,
       o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet,
       MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END) AS max_g_mag,
       MIN(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END) AS min_g_mag,
       MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 2 THEN f.value END) AS max_r_mag,
       MIN(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 2 THEN f.value END) AS min_r_mag,
       (MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END) - MIN(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 1 THEN f.value END)) AS delta_mag_g,
       (MAX(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 2 THEN f.value END) - MIN(CASE WHEN f.name = 'g-r_max_corr' AND f.fid = 2 THEN f.value END)) AS delta_mag_r
FROM object o
JOIN agn_oids a ON o.oid = a.oid
JOIN valid_objects v ON o.oid = v.oid
JOIN magnitude_variations m ON o.oid = m.oid
JOIN feature f ON o.oid = f.oid
GROUP BY o.oid, f.value, f.name, f.version, f.fid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet
HAVING delta_mag_g > 1 AND delta_mag_r > 0.5;

-- First, we need to find the ALLWISE match for the ZTF object 'ZTF19aascdol'.
-- We will use a subquery to get the OID from the 'object' table for the ZTF object.
-- Then, we will use the Q3C extension to calculate the distance between the ZTF object and its ALLWISE counterpart.

WITH ztf_object AS (
    SELECT oid, ra, dec
    FROM object
    WHERE oid = 'ZTF19aascdol'
),
allwise_match AS (
    SELECT a.oid_catalog, a.ra, a.dec, a.w1mpro, a.w2mpro, a.w3mpro, a.w4mpro
    FROM allwise a
    JOIN ztf_object z ON q3c_join(z.ra, z.dec, a.ra, a.dec, 0.1) -- Assuming a small radius for matching
)
SELECT 
    z.oid AS ztf_identifier,
    a.oid_catalog AS allwise_identifier,
    q3c_dist(z.ra, z.dec, a.ra, a.dec) AS distance_between_counterparts,
    a.w1mpro AS w1_magnitude,
    a.w2mpro AS w2_magnitude,
    a.w3mpro AS w3_magnitude,
    a.w4mpro AS w4_magnitude
FROM ztf_object z
JOIN allwise_match a ON true;

WITH bogus_oids AS
  (SELECT oid,
          probability AS prob_stamp_bogus
   FROM probability
   WHERE class_name = 'bogus'
     AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
     AND classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
     AND probability > 0.7 ), -- Subquery to get OIDs with probability > 0.9 for 'Transient' in 'lc_classifier_top'

          probability AS prob_lc_transient
   FROM probability
   WHERE class_name = 'Transient'
     AND classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_top'
     AND probability > 0.9 ) -- Main query to select the required columns

       o.ndet AS number_of_detections,
       o.firstmjd AS first_detection_date,
       b.prob_stamp_bogus,
       t.prob_lc_transient
FROM OBJECT o
JOIN bogus_oids b ON o.oid = b.oid
JOIN transient_oids t ON o.oid = t.oid
WHERE o.ndet > 10
ORDER BY b.oid
LIMIT 30;

           ms.magmax_corr, ms.magmin_corr, (ms.magmax_corr - ms.magmin_corr) AS max_rise
    FROM detection d
    JOIN r_band_magstats ms ON d.oid = ms.oid
    WHERE d.fid = 2 -- r-band filter
      AND d.oid IN (SELECT oid FROM filtered_objects)
)
-- Select the first 1000 rows ordered by object identifier
SELECT *
FROM result
ORDER BY oid
LIMIT 1000;
